"| 107,225\n| style=\"text-align: right;\"| 4,644\n| style=\"text-align: right;\"| 410,583\n|-{{Party shading/Democratic}}\n! style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 75%;\" | percent\n| style=\"text-align: right;\"| '''37.63%'''\n| style=\"text-align: right;\"| 35.12%\n| style=\"text-align: right;\"| 26.12%\n| style=\"text-align: right;\"| 1.13%\n| style=\"text-align: right;\"| 100.00%\n|}\n\n===Analysis===\n[[Montana]] was won by Governor [[Bill Clinton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Arkansas]]) with 37.63% of the popular vote over incumbent President [[George H. W. Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Texas]]) with 35.12%. Businessman [[Ross Perot]] ([[Independent politician|I]]-Texas) finished in third, with 26.12% of the popular vote.<ref name=results/> It was the first time the state voted for a Democrat since it was won by President [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] in [[1964 United States presidential election in Montana|1964]]. It is also the last time that the state voted Democratic ({{As of|2016|11|alt=as of the [[2016 United States presidential election|2016 presidential election]]}}), as well as the last time that [[Sanders County, Montana|Sanders County]] and [[Valley County, Montana|Valley County]] voted Democratic.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{State Results of the 1992 U.S. presidential election}}\n{{United States elections, 1992}}\n[[Category:1992 United States presidential election by state|Montana]]\n[[Category:United States presidential elections in Montana|1992]]\n[[Category:1992 Montana elections]]\n", "text_old": "{{main|1992 United States presidential election}}\n{{Infobox Election\n| election_name = [[1992 United States presidential election|United States presidential election]] in Montana, 1992\n| country = Montana\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = United States presidential election in Montana, 1988\n| previous_year = 1988\n| next_election = United States presidential election in Montana, 1996\n| next_year = 1996\n| election_date = November 3, 1992\n| image_size = x160px\n| image1 = Bill Clinton.jpg\n| nominee1 = '''[[Bill Clinton]]'''\n| party1 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| home_state1 = [[Arkansas]]\n| running_mate1 = '''[[Al Gore]]'''\n| electoral_vote1 = '''3'''\n| popular_vote1 = '''154,507'''\n| percentage1 = '''37.63%'''\n| image2 = George H. W. Bush presidential portrait (cropped 2).jpg\n| nominee2 = [[George H. W. Bush]] \n| party2 = Republican Party (United States)\n| home_state2 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate2 = [[Dan Quayle]]\n| electoral_vote2 = 0\n| popular_vote2 = 144,207\n| percentage2 = 35.12%\t\n| image3 = RossPerotColor.jpg\n| nominee3 = [[Ross Perot]]\n| party3 = Independent (politician)\n| home_state3 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate3 = [[James Stockdale]]\n| electoral_vote3 = 0\n| popular_vote3 = 107,225\t   \n| percentage3 = 26.12%\n| title = President\n| before_election = [[George H. W. Bush]]\n| before_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| after_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| map_image         = File:Montana1992good.png\n| map_size          = 350px\n| map_caption       = County Results<ref> http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/ </ref>\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Clinton'''\n{{legend|#d3e7ff|30\u201340%}}\n{{legend|#b9d7ff|40\u201350%}}\n{{legend|#86b6f2|50\u201360%}}\n{{legend|#4389e3|60\u201370%}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Bush'''\n{{legend|#ffccd0|30\u201340%}}\n{{legend|#f2b3be|40\u201350%}}\n{{legend|#e27f90|50\u201360%}}\n{{col-end}}\n| map2_image         = File:Montana 1992 presidential results by county.png\n| map2_size          = 350px\n| map2_caption       = Results by county showing number of votes by size and candidates by color. <ref name=Cooney1992/>\n}}\n\n{{ElectionsMT}}\n\nThe '''1992 United States presidential election in Montana''' was won on November 3, 1992, by [[List of governors of Arkansas|Governor]] [[Bill Clinton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Arkansas]]) with a 37.63% of the popular vote plurality over incumbent [[President of the United States|President]] [[George H. W. Bush]]'s ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Texas]]) 35.12%, and businessman [[Ross Perot]]'s ([[Independent politician|I]]-Texas) 26.12%.<ref name=results/> All of [[Montana]]'s three [[United States Electoral College|electoral votes]] were assigned to Clinton, contributing to his 370 to 168 electoral vote win of the [[1992 United States presidential election|1992 presidential election]].<ref>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/national.php?year=1992|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=8 June 2012}}</ref> To date, this is the most recent presidential election in which Montana was won by the Democratic candidate. \n\n==Results==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"\n! colspan=\"6\" | United States presidential election in Montana, 1992<ref name=results>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results - Montana|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/state.php?year=1992&off=0&elect=0&fips=30&f=0|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=8 June 2012}}</ref>\n|-bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\" align=\"center\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15em\" |Party\n! style=\"width: 17em\" |Candidate\n! style=\"width: 5em\" |Votes\n! style=\"width: 7em\" |Percentage\n! style=\"width: 5em\" |Electoral votes\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#3333FF; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | '''[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]'''\n| '''[[Bill Clinton]]'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''154,507'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''37.63%'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''3'''\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FF3333; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| [[George H.W. Bus